-- Carige shareholder placing stake at 0.435-0.48 euros/shr - source
-- 
-- Tue May 20, 2014 12:38PM EDT
-- None



MILAN, May 20 (Reuters) - The top foundation shareholder of Italy's Banca Carige <CRGI.MI> is placing a 15 percent stake in the lender in a range of 0.435 to 0.48 euros per share, a market source said on Tuesday.

Banca IMI and Credit Suisse Securities are joint-bookrunners of the offer which is reserved for institutional investors.